definition: to fill or stuff/(of a form etc) to fill in

sentences.english: Which but to-day by feeding is allayed.
sentences.chinese: 今天减少是因为填满了沟壑。

sentences.english: Wang and his roommates used 10 buckets of water to fill the inflatable pool.
sentences.chinese: 王晓星和室友们用了10桶水才把充气泳池填满。

sentences.english: It's going to take a lot of pictures of the kids to fill that up.
sentences.chinese: 那得需要很多小孩子的照片才能把那块硬盘填满。

sentences.english: Only very thrifty chirdren manage to fill up a money-box.
sentences.chinese: 只有非常节俭的儿童才会设法填满一个储蓄罐。

sentences.english: All requests for image data are filled from the memory store.
sentences.chinese: 会由记忆体存放区填满所有影像资料要求。

sentences.english: Soon the hat stpaintinged to fill up.
sentences.chinese: 帽子很快的开始填满了钱。

sentences.english: As the mood of the festival set in, laughter and role playing antics filled the campus.
sentences.chinese: 孩子与家长们的欢笑声填满了校园。

sentences.english: The driller filled the grill with superb film.
sentences.chinese: 钻孔者在烤架上填满光线的胶片。

sentences.english: Continue to fill the system until the coolant tank is full.
sentences.chinese: 持续填注冷却系统，直到冷却剂贮藏箱填满。

sentences.english: I will fill my heart with the silence and endure it.
sentences.chinese: 我将用你的沉默填满心房，并忍受它。

sentences.english: When they met in the church tower the gaps in their fragmentary conversation were filled up.
sentences.chinese: 到了教堂的钟楼，他们零碎谈话的空隙才算给填满。

sentences.english: Within two weeks I had filled the remaining vacancies in the cabinet.
sentences.chinese: 两周时间里，我填满了内阁剩下的所有空缺。

sentences.english: Give me reason , to fill this hole, connect the space between.
sentences.chinese: 给我理由，填满沟壑，将这断路铺平。

sentences.english: Let me fill you with love and joy, and we will meet again.
sentences.chinese: 让我再次为你填满爱与喜乐，我们将会再见。

sentences.english: She spaced her appointments throughout the day.
sentences.chinese: 她将各种约会间隔排开，填满一日。

sentences.english: The TV also showed images of several water-filled craters caused by the blasts.
sentences.chinese: 电视还播放了一些填满水的被炸弹炸穿的弹孔的画面。
